(ABSTRACT) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(This memo documents the methodology of human-AI collaborative design as) show newline
(practiced in the development of Cyberspace. The central insight: shared) show newline
(context enables high-bandwidth communication. When both parties) show newline
(understand the domain vocabulary, complex ideas compress to single) show newline
(words, and conversation operates on deltas rather than explanations.) show newline
() show newline
(This is not a description of a tool. It is a case study in a new form of) show newline
(collaboration, with Cyberspace as the artifact and the commit history as) show newline
(evidence.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(1. THE BANDWIDTH PROBLEM) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Normal technical conversation has O\(n\) overhead. Every concept requires) show newline
(explanation. Every term needs definition. Context must be re-established) show newline
(with each interaction.) show newline
() show newline
(This creates a ceiling on complexity. Discussions stay shallow because) show newline
(depth requires shared foundation that doesn't exist.) show newline
() show newline
(The alternative: build the foundation incrementally. Each conversation) show newline
(adds to shared context. Each term defined becomes a compression key.) show newline
(Over time, communication complexity shifts from O\(n\) to O\(delta\) - just) show newline
(the changes.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(2. VOCABULARY AS COMPRESSION) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Cyberspace developed a domain vocabulary through iterative design:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(  Term        Compressed Meaning                                                                           ) show newline
(  soup        Newton-style persistent object store, vault browser, content-addressed storage               ) show newline
(  weave       The distributed system as a whole, nodes connected, lambdas flowing                          ) show newline
(  forge       Build system, password generation, incremental compilation, JIT - all metallurgical shaping  ) show newline
(  smelter     Raw material refinement - word lists to digraph statistics, source to compiled modules       ) show newline
(  residents   Editors that extend top-level, blade guards disengaged, Murphy/Shrayer heritage              ) show newline
(  seal        Cryptographic commitment, hash chain, immutability guarantee                                 ) show newline
(  realm       Trust domain, capability scope, federated identity boundary                                  ) show newline
(  wilderness  The space between realms, untrusted, discovery zone                                          ) show newline
() show newline
(Each term carries history. 'Forge' invokes Gasser's Multics work,) show newline
(Piper/Callas at DEC, VMS 6.0. One word, forty years of context.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(3. THE ITERATIVE LOOP) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(The collaboration follows a pattern:) show newline
() show newline
(  * Human provides vision and constraints - what should exist, what matters, what the heritage requires) show newline
(  * AI provides implementation and exploration - code, alternatives, edge cases discovered) show newline
(  * Human evaluates and refines - 'keep it', 'too ugly', 'add author credit') show newline
(  * AI incorporates and extends - the delta applied, implications traced) show newline
(  * Context accumulates - next iteration starts from higher ground) show newline
() show newline
(Neither party could build this alone. The human has the vision and) show newline
(heritage but not the bandwidth for implementation. The AI has the) show newline
(bandwidth but not the taste or history. Together: vision realized at) show newline
(scale.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(4. DELTA COMMUNICATION) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Examples from a single session \(2026-01-28\):) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    User: "lambda completions broken at open paren") show newline
(    AI: [knows: lineage-src.c, findLastWord, paren_wrap mode, completion callback]) show newline
(        [understands: user typed '\(sta', TAB failed, need '\(' as word boundary]) show newline
(        [fixes: one line change to findLastWord, rebuild, test, commit]) show newline
() show newline
(No explanation needed. 'Lambda completions' identifies the subsystem.) show newline
('Open paren' identifies the boundary condition. The fix is obvious given) show newline
(shared context.) show newline
() show newline
(Contrast with cold start:) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(    User: "When I type open paren then 'sta' and press TAB in the) show newline
(           Scheme REPL using the linenoise-based line editor with) show newline
(           command completion enabled in schemer mode where completions) show newline
(           should be wrapped in parentheses, the completion doesn't) show newline
(           trigger because the word-finding function only splits on) show newline
(           spaces, not on open parentheses, so it sees '\(sta' as the) show newline
(           word to complete rather than 'sta'...") show newline
() show newline
(Same information. 10x the words. That's the compression ratio of shared) show newline
(context.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
(5. CONTEXT AS FORCE MULTIPLIER) show newline
(------------------------------------------------------------------------) show newline
() show newline
(Accumulated context changes what's possible:) show newline
() show newline
(  * First session: explain SPKI, explain vaults, explain why Scheme) show newline
(  * Tenth session: 'add seek to command aliases' - done in seconds) show newline
(  * Hundredth session: 'residents with prefixes, blade guards, heritage credits' - complete spec) show newline
() show newline
(The collaboration gets more powerful over time. Each session builds on) show newline
(all previous sessions. The shared dictionary grows. Compression) show newline
(improves. Bandwidth increases.) show newline
() show newline
(This is the opposite of typical tool use, where each session starts) show newline
(fresh.) show newline
() show newline
() show newline
